The Zondo Commission is expected to resume its work at the end of June or early July. That's according to Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo who briefed the media about the way forward for the State Capture Inquiry a short while ago. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo says plans are underway for the state capture commission to resume with public hearings towards the end of June. The Deputy Chief Justice was briefing the media on the work of the commission during the lockdown period. The commission has been out of action since 17 March due to the coronavirus outbreak. READ: Level 3 and Level 4 regulations declared unconstitutional Zondo says the commission is determined to meet its March 2021 deadline. In February, the court granted the Zondo commission a final extension to complete its work by 31 March 2021.